[During the most recent meeting of EC's PAFF Committee on Animal Health & Welfare, held 15 Dec 2021, the following 9 countries presented their PowerPoint reports on HPAI in poultry and wildlife, covering the chronology, maps, surveillance and control measures, etc. Their respective links, and excerpted data on HPAI in wild birds, follow. Almost all tested wild birds were infected by HPAI H5N1; residual cases of H5N8, the subtype which had been circulating during several previous seasons, were still recorded in the Czech Republic and Sweden.

- Czech Republic: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_cze.pdf (wild birds: 15 cases H5N1; during 2021, also cases of H5N8, H5N5)
- France: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_fra.pdf (wild birds: 9 cases H5N1)
- Germany: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_deu.pdf (wild birds: 327 cases H5N1)
- Hungary: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_hun.pdf (wild birds: 5 cases H5N1)
- Ireland: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_ire.pdf (wild birds: 57 cases H5N1)
- Italy: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_ita.pdf (wild birds: 8 cases H5N1)
- Poland: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_pol.pdf (wild birds: 6 cases H5N1)
- Portugal: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_prt.pdf (wild birds: not presented)
- Sweden: https://ec.europa.eu/food/system/files/2021-12/reg-com_ahw_20211215_hpai_swe.pdf (wild birds: 13 cases H5N1; 1 case H5N8)

A map, presenting Europe's officially reported HPAI H5N1 outbreaks in poultry and cases in wild birds, since 1 Oct 2021 and as of 6 Jan 2022, is available at https://www.fli.de/fileadmin/FLI/Images/Tierseuchengeschehen/H5N8/Karten_EU/2022/Map_AI_EU_2022-01-06.jpg. - Mod.AS]

