[The continuing HPAI H5N1 panzootic, which started in the fall of 2021, has reportedly caused at least 3 other mass mortality events in wild birds:

- Cormorants in Dyer Island, South Africa (https://mg.co.za/environment/2021-10-20-bird-flu-outbreak-on-dyer-island-causing-mass-deaths/);
- Demoiselle cranes in Rajasthan, India (https://www.wti.org.in/news/wti-team-on-ground-as-avian-flu-hits-demoiselle-cranes-in-rajasthan/);
- Barnacle geese in Solway Firth, Scotland (https://www.scotsman.com/news/people/bird-flu-fears-around-4000-deaths-in-biggest-outbreak-for-years-3501424; see 20220106.8700696).

The HPAI H5N1 panzootic and its impact upon agriculture, public health and wildlife conservation prescribe the need for a One Health approach. - Mod.AS

